article.headline: Utah Valley State 72, Cleveland St. 65
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Ronnie Price scored 34 points to lead Utah Valley State past Cleveland State 72-65 Saturday. Price led Utah Valley State on a 16-4 run in the second half, scoring 11 as the Wolverines (2-6) pulled ahead 51-44 and held on for just their second win of the season. Omari Westley, who was held scoreless in the first half, led the Vikings (3-3) with 16 points and 11 rebounds, but Cleveland State couldn't make up for 22 turnovers. The Vikings outrebounded the Wolverines 41-26, but also committed 25 fouls to Utah Valley State's 17. Russell Wesley scored 14 and Pierre Thomas finished with 11 points for the Wolverines. Raheem Moss scored 13 for Cleveland State, which led by two points at halftime and pulled ahead by five early in the second half before the Wolverines rallied, shooting 52 percent from the floor.
